<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="313" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1472,2039]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1509,1535]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Etymology</emphasis>
: The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johansson" authorityYear="2021" box="[462,579,1508,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anatolicus">
<emphasis box="[462,579,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">anatolicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the region 
<collectingCountry box="[886,982,1508,1534]" name="Turkey" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1018,1098,1508,1534]" name="Turkey" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Turkey</collectingCountry>
where the 
<typeStatus box="[1224,1272,1509,1535]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">type</typeStatus>
specimen was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="313" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1472,2039]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1580,1606]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: A very distinct species. Most simliar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Johansson, 2021" authorityName="Johansson" authorityYear="2021" box="[764,905,1580,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castilloae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[764,905,1580,1607]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">O. castilloae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[911,999,1581,1607]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which also has the radius strongly bent before the junction with the pterostigma, however with the face narrower and the ocelli touching the inner margin of the compound eye. Similar also to 
<taxonomicName authority="Brauns" authorityName="Brauns" authorityYear="1895" box="[574,826,1652,1679]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis box="[574,737,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Ophion dispar</emphasis>
Brauns
</taxonomicName>
, which has the radius straight before the junction with the pterostigma, and the spiracle of the first tergite further anterior of the sclerotized hind margin of the first sternite (
<figureCitation box="[160,262,1724,1751]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1691,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1667]" captionTargetId="figure-21@16.[151,1436,181,1667]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. A) Ophion castilloae sp. nov. paratype female (NMNL), habitus lateral view; B) Ophion castilloae sp. nov. paratype female, head anterior view; C) Ophion castilloae sp. nov. paratype female, head, dorsal view; D) Ophion dispar Brauns, 1895, female (NMNL), petiolus lateral view; E) Ophion castilloae sp. nov. paratype female, scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; E) Ophion castilloae sp. nov. paratype female, petiolus lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226052/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="315" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1472,2039]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="314" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1760,1786]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Description</emphasis>
: Male unknown. Fore wing length 
<quantity box="[752,837,1761,1787]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[1002,1087,1760,1787]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
. Antennae broken, the longest stump with 45 flagellomeres. Temple slightly buccate behind compound eyes, in lateral view about 0.6 × as long as compound eye (
<figureCitation box="[333,423,1832,1859]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-146@13.[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Ophion anatolicus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM).A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) epicnemial carina, ventrolateral view; E) head, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226044/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
). Malar space narrow, 0.1 × the width of the mandibular base. Space between compound eye and lateral ocellus narrow, about 0.1 × the diameter of ocellus (
<figureCitation box="[925,1015,1868,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-146@13.[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Ophion anatolicus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM).A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) epicnemial carina, ventrolateral view; E) head, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226044/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
). Face relatively wide (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1373,1868,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-146@13.[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Ophion anatolicus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM).A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) epicnemial carina, ventrolateral view; E) head, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226044/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
). Occipital carina dorsally evenly curved. Face below antennal sockets distinctly and densely punctate, punctures often merging. Clypeus with large, deep but significantly scarcer punctures than the face, polished. Mandibular gape right angled, with internal angles. First flagellomere 3.5 × as long as wide. Central flagellomeres about 1.8 × as long as wide. Mesoscutum polished with very dense and distinct punctures, space between punctures at most equal to their diameter. Mesopleuron polished with very dense and distinct punctures. Epicnemial carina, in antero-ventral view, with pleurosternal angles obtuse, distinctly anterior to sternal angles (
<figureCitation box="[942,1033,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-146@13.[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Ophion anatolicus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM).A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) epicnemial carina, ventrolateral view; E) head, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226044/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
). Scutellum without lateral carinae. Propodeum weakly rugulose with only the posterior transverse carina present, ventrally with a longitudinal shallow furrow (
<figureCitation box="[244,334,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-146@13.[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Ophion anatolicus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM).A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) epicnemial carina, ventrolateral view; E) head, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226044/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
). Sclerotised part of first sternite ending distinctly anterior to spiracle. Hind trochantellus shorter than wide in dorsal view. Hind femur slender, about 7.0 × as long as wide. Inner spur of hind tibia about 0.5 × as long as hind metatarsus. Wing membrane clear. Ramellus short, reaching 0.1–0.2 of the width of the discosubmarginal cell. Outer part of radius straight, weakly curved apically. Radius conspicuously bent and widened before junction with pterostigma (
<figureCitation box="[356,445,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-146@13.[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Ophion anatolicus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM).A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) epicnemial carina, ventrolateral view; E) head, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226044/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
). Nervellus broken slightly above the middle by the discoidella.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226044" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5226044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226044/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" startId="13.[151,250,1966,1990]" targetBox="[164,1423,453,1943]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1966,2026]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1966,1990]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">FIGURE 9.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Johansson, 2021" authorityName="Johansson" authorityYear="2021" box="[281,469,1966,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anatolicus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[281,469,1966,1990]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Ophion anatolicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[475,554,1967,1990]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
holotype female (OÖLM). A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) epicnemial carina, ventrolateral view; E) head, anterior view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,321]" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">
<emphasis box="[199,336,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">Colouration</emphasis>
: Body yellow reddish. Inner and outer orbits narrowly yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1087,1218,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-146@13.[164,1423,453,1943]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Ophion anatolicus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM).A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, dorsal view; D) epicnemial carina, ventrolateral view; E) head, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226044/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">Figs 9A–E</figureCitation>
). Mandibular teeth black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,223,249]" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">Remarks</emphasis>
: A member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1829" box="[517,679,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventricosus">
<emphasis box="[517,679,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">O. ventricosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,364,258,285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">DNA Barcode</emphasis>
: The DNA barcode sequences of the 
<typeStatus box="[783,881,259,285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Johansson, 2021" authorityName="Johansson" authorityYear="2021" box="[918,1126,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anatolicus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[918,1126,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">Ophion anatolicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1133,1219,259,285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="315" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are available at the BOLD systems database: sample id. NJP737, sequence id. LNU2573-21.
</paragraph>
